    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Trim the ends from your <strong>Brussels sprouts </strong>and cut <strong>half</strong> the sprouts in half (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
